{
  "texts": [
    "We introduce additional training constraints to encourage encodings to be dense as described in Methods.",
    "At the end of the second training stage, the Encoder is able to suppress artifacts in EM images.",
    "After a given resolution scale Aligner/Encoder pair has finished training, it is used to process the whole training dataset to produce displacement fields that will be used for subsequent resolution scales training.",
    "Training of multi-resolution hierarchies of Aligner/Encoder pairs is implemented in the metroEM package released with this work.",
    "Online Field Finetuner refines the initial displacement field through gradient descent."
  ]
}